Binary Classification with NN

Benoit and Sarat

20/04/2023

Breast cancer Data

load("Breast_cancer.RData")
dim(Breast_cancer_data)
[1] 569  32
data <- Breast_cancer_data[,-1]

Split the data

set.seed(101)
indexes <- sample(1:569, 456 )
train_data <- data[indexes, ]
test_data <- data[-indexes, ]
trainX <- train_data[, -1]
trainY <- train_data[, 1]
testX <- test_data[, -1]
testY <- test_data[, 1]
trainY <- ifelse(trainY == "B", 0, 1)
testY <- ifelse(testY == "B", 0, 1)

Neural Network as logistic model

data.glm <- data.frame(Y=trainY,trainX)
NN1 <- glm(Y~.,data=data.glm,family=binomial)
Warning: glm.fit: algorithm did not converge
Warning: glm.fit: fitted probabilities numerically 0 or 1 occurred
class.pred <- function(x){
pred <- ifelse(x < 0.5, 0, 1)
pred <- factor(pred,levels = c(0,1))
return(pred)
}
data.test <- data.frame(Y=testY,testX)
data.train <- data.frame(Y=trainY,trainX)
  • Train
predt <- class.pred(predict(NN1,newdata =data.train ))
table(Prediction=predt,Reality=trainY)
          Reality
Prediction   0   1
         0 284   0
         1   0 172
  • Test
pred <- class.pred(predict(NN1,newdata =data.test ))
table(Prediction=pred,Reality=testY)
          Reality
Prediction  0  1
         0 65  4
         1  8 36

Should we add a layer ?

library(neuralnet)
nn1 <- neuralnet(Y~.,data=data.glm,hidden=4,linear.output=FALSE)
plot(nn1, rep="best")

pr.nn <- compute(nn1,data.test)
pred <- class.pred(pr.nn$net.result[,1])
table(Prediction=pred,Reality=testY)
          Reality
Prediction  0  1
         0 67  0
         1  6 40
  • Number of parameters
length(unlist(nn1$weights))
[1] 129

More neurons ?

Should we add a second layer ?

nn2 <- neuralnet(Y~.,data=data.glm,hidden=c(4,2),linear.output=FALSE)
plot(nn2, rep="best")

pr.nn <- compute(nn2,data.test)
pred <- class.pred(pr.nn$net.result[,1])
table(Prediction=pred,Reality=testY)
          Reality
Prediction  0  1
         0 68  6
         1  5 34
